etymologies: early 17th century (in gasket (sense 2)): perhaps from French garcette ‘thin rope’ (originally ‘little girl’), diminutive of garce, feminine of gars ‘boy’

definitions: a shaped piece or ring of rubber or other material sealing the junction between two surfaces in an engine or other device

examples.text: oil was leaking from the gasket between the drive flange and the hub

shortDefinitions: shaped sheet or ring of rubber or other material sealing junction between two surfaces in engine

definitions: a cord securing a furled sail to the yard, boom, or gaff of a sailing vessel.
shortDefinitions: cord securing furled sail to yard of sailing ship
